Generalize overlap-add to support arbitrary JACK period sizes. Upstream already
computed multiplier = SIZE / n_samples correctly but then overrode it with
hardcoded values for 128/256 only, and the overlap-add output block used the
same 128/256-only if/else — producing silence for any other period size.

Remove the redundant overrides and replace the if/else output section with the
same generalized single-buffer loop used in cabsim-lv2.

Also remove oA/oB/oC overlap buffers that were only used by the broken
128-sample branch, and fix the spurious duplicate-const on the `in` pointer.
